          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-375-371L-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-375-371L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-375-371L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-1" n="1">A Lady wise as well as fair,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-2" n="2">Whose Conscience was her only Care;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-3" n="3">Thoughtful upon a point of moment</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-4" n="4">Woud know y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Text as well as coment</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-5" n="5">Hearing of a grave divine</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-6" n="6">She sent to bid him come and dine</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-7" n="7">Now you must know he was not quite</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-8" n="8">So grave as to be unpolite</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-9" n="9">Thought human Learning wou'd not Lessen</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-10" n="10">The Dignity of his profession;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-11" n="11">And if you heard y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> man discourse</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-12" n="12">Or preach you'd like him neer y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> worse</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-13" n="13">He long had bid y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Court farewell,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-14" n="14">Retreating silent to his cell;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-15" n="15">Suspected for y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Love he bore</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-16" n="16">For one who sway'd sometime before:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-17" n="17">Which made it more surprizing how</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-18" n="18">He shou'd be sent for thither now.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-19" n="19">The Message told, he Gapes he Stares</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-20" n="20">And scarce beleives his Eyes and Ears;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-21" n="21">Cou'd not conceive what it cou'd mean,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-22" n="22">And fain wou'd hear it told again.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-23" n="23">But then the Esq<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> so trim and nice</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-24" n="24">'Twere rude to make him tell it twice</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-25" n="25">So bow'd was thankful for y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Honour</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-26" n="26">And wou'd not fail to wait upon her</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-27" n="27">His Beaver bru\<hi rend="italics">del</hi>·i\sh'd his shoes &amp; gown</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-28" n="28">Away he trudges into Town.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-29" n="29">Passes y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Lower Castle Yard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-30" n="30">And now advancing to y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Guard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-31" n="31">He trembles at y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> thoughts of State</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-32" n="32">For Conscious of a Sheepish gate</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-33" n="33">His Spirits of a Sudden fail'd him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-34" n="34">He stop'd and cou'd not tell what ail'd him.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-35" n="35">What was the Message I rec<hi rend="superscript">ḍ</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-36" n="36">Why certainly y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Capt<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> rav'd.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-37" n="37">To dine with her and come at 3</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-38" n="38">Jmpossible it cannot be.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-39" n="39">Or may be J mistook y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> word</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-40" n="40">My Lady──────── It must be my Lord!</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-41" n="41">My Lord's abroad, my Lady too</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-42" n="42">What must the unhappy D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> do?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-43" n="43">Js Cap<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> Crachrode here pray? No:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-44" n="44">Nay then tis time for me to go.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-45" n="45">Am I awake, or do I dream?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-46" n="46">I'm sure he call'd me by my name</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-47" n="47">Nam'd me as plain as he cou'd speak</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-48" n="48">And yet there must be some mistake</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-49" n="49">Why what a jest must J have been</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-50" n="50">Now had my Lady been within</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-51" n="51">What cou'd I've said── Jm mighty glad</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-52" n="52">She went abroad── She'd thought me mad.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-53" n="53">The hour of Dining now is past</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-54" n="54">Well then I'll een go home and fast,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-55" n="55">And think I scap'd being made a Scoff</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-56" n="56">J think Jm very fairly off.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-57" n="57">My Lady now returning home</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-58" n="58">Calld Crachrode is y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> come</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-59" n="59">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-60" n="60">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-61" n="61">The Cap<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> walks about &amp; Searches</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-62" n="62">Tho' all y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Rooms &amp; Courts &amp; Arches.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-63" n="63">Examines all y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Servants round</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-64" n="64">In vain no D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> to be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-65" n="65">My Lady cou'd not chuse but wonder</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-66" n="66">Capt. I fear you've made a blunder──</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-67" n="67">But pray to morrow go at ten</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-68" n="68">I'll try his manners once agen</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-69" n="69">If rudeness be th' Effect of Knowledge,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-70" n="70">My son shall never see a College.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-71" n="71">This Capt<hi rend="superscript">ṇ</hi> was a man of Reading,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-72" n="72">And much good sence as well as breeding</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-73" n="73">Who loth to blame or to incense</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-74" n="74">Said little in his own defence</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-75" n="75">Next day another message bro<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-76" n="76">The D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> frighted at his fault</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-77" n="77">Is dress'd and stealing thrô y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Croud</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-78" n="78">Now pale as Death now flush'd &amp; bow'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-79" n="79">Panting &amp; faultring── humm'd &amp; haw'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-80" n="80">Her Ladyship was gone abroad────</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-81" n="81">The Captain too── He did not know</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-82" n="82">Whether he ought to stay or go</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-83" n="83">Beg'd she'd forgive him── in Conclusion</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-84" n="84">My Lady pitying his Confusion,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-85" n="85">Call'd her good nature to relieve him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-86" n="86">Told him she thought she might believe him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-87" n="87">And would not only grant his suit</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-88" n="88">But visit him and eat some fruit</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-89" n="89">Provided at a proper time</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-90" n="90">He told y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> real truth in Rhime</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-91" n="91">Twas to no purpose to oppose</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-92" n="92">She'd hear of no excuse in prose,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-93" n="93">The D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> stood not on debate</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-94" n="94">Glad to Compound at any rate,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-95" n="95">So bowing seemingly comply'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-96" n="96">Thô if he durst he had deny'd.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-97" n="97">But <hi rend="superscript">s</hi>1<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> resolv'd to show his taste</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-98" n="98">Was too refin'd to give a feast</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-99" n="99">He'd treat w<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.  nothing that was rare</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-100" n="100">But winding walks &amp; purer air</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-101" n="101">He's entertain w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi>out expence</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-102" n="102">Or pride of vain magnificence</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-103" n="103">For well he knew to such a guest</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-104" n="104">The plainest meals must be y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> best</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-105" n="105">To stomachs cloy'd w<hi rend="superscript">tḥ</hi> costly fare</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-106" n="106">Simplicity alone is rare.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-107" n="107">Whilst high and nice &amp; curious meats</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-108" n="108">Are really but vulgar treats</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-109" n="109">Jnstead of spoils of Persian Looms,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-110" n="110">The Costly boast of regal Rooms,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-111" n="111">Thought it more courtly &amp; discreet,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-112" n="112">To scatter Roses at her Feet</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-113" n="113">Roses of richest dye that shone</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-114" n="114">With native lustre like her own.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-115" n="115">Beauty w<hi rend="superscript">cḥ</hi> needs no aid of art</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-116" n="116">Thrô every sense to reach y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> heart</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-117" n="117">The Gracious dame, althô she knew</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-118" n="118">All This was much beneath her due</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-119" n="119">Lik'd every thing at Last thought fit</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-120" n="120">To praise par maniere d'acquit</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-121" n="121">But yet thô seeming pleas'd can't bear</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-122" n="122">The scorching Sun &amp; chilling air</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-123" n="123">Frighted alike at both extremes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-124" n="124">If he displays or hides his beams</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-125" n="125">Thô seeming pleas'd at all she sees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-126" n="126">Starts at y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> rustling of y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Trees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-127" n="127">Can scarcely speak for want of Breath</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-128" n="128">Jn half a walk fatigu'd to Death</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-129" n="129">The D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> takes his hint from hence</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-130" n="130">To Vindicate his late offence.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-131" n="131">Mad<hi rend="superscript">ṃ</hi> y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> mighty power of use</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-132" n="132">Now strongly pleads in my excuse;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-133" n="133">If you unus'd have scarcely strength</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-134" n="134">To move this walk's uncrouded length</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-135" n="135">If rattling in a scene so rude</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-136" n="136">Thrô long disuse of Solitude</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-137" n="137">If long confi'd to fire &amp; Skreens</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-138" n="138">You dre\<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·a\d y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> waving of these greens</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-139" n="139">If Trees that neither \<hi rend="italics">del·?</hi>speak·<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·see\ nor hear</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-140" n="140">Nor speak nor walk can give you fear</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-141" n="141">If You who long have breath'd y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi>: fumes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-142" n="142">Of City Fogs and crouded Rooms</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-143" n="143">Do now Solicitously shun</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-144" n="144">The Cooler air and dazling sun</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-145" n="145">If Sols majestick Eye you flee</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-146" n="146">Learn hence t'excuse &amp; pity me.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-147" n="147">Consider what it is to bear</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-148" n="148">The powder'd Courtiers witty sneer</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-149" n="149">To see th'Important man of Dress</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-150" n="150">Snouching my College aukardness</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-151" n="151">To be y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Strutting Cornet's sport</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-152" n="152">To run y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Gauntlet of y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Court</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-153" n="153">Winning my way by slow approaches</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-154" n="154">Thrô crouds of Coxcombs &amp; of Coaches</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-155" n="155">From y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> <hi rend="superscript">s</hi>1<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> fierce cockaded Centry</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-156" n="156">Quite thrô y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> tribe of waiting Gentry</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-157" n="157">To pass so many crouded Stages</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-158" n="158">And stand y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Staring of y<hi rend="superscript">ẹ</hi> Pages</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-159" n="159">And after all to crown my spleen</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-160" n="160">Be told──── You are not to be seen</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-161" n="161">Or if you are, be forc'd to bear</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-162" n="162">The Awe of that Majestick air</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-163" n="163">And can J then be guilty found</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-164" n="164">Jn Dreading y<hi rend="superscript">ṣ</hi> Vexatious round</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-165" n="165">Can it be Strange if I eschew</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-166" n="166">A scene so glaring &amp; so new</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-167" n="167">Or is he Criminal that flyes</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-375-371L-line-168" n="168">The living lustre of your Eyes.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
